      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl11_LabelType\">You had a close encounter with a servant or worshiper of Andoletta who provided you with a memorable, if unconventional, consolation after a loss.</span></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTraits_ctl00_LabelName\"><strong>Requirements</strong></span></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl11_LabelType\">Andoletta</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl11_LabelType\">As a result, you gain a +2 trait bonus on saving throws against emotion and fear effects. If you are immune to fear, you instead gain a +4 trait bonus on saves against emotion effects.</span></p>",
